retired gen richard secord 
accused of working as a middleman in the irancontra affair said 
thursday he neither expects nor wants a pardon from president 
reagan because one isnt necessary 
i didnt break any laws so why would there be any pardon 
he told the palm beach post before addressing the young republicans 
of the palm beaches 
i think we did the right thing im not embarrassed about what 
we did how we did it secord said i think we will prevail 
secord and iranianborn businessman albert hakim are accused of 
helping set up the armsforhostages deal that prosecutors said was 
orchestrated by former white house aides oliver north and john 
poindexter 
the four were indicted in march on charges of conspiring to 
divert profits from the arms sales to nicaraguas contras at a time 
when most aid to the rebels was prohibited 
