<TEXT>
british sugar refiner tate amp lyle 
plc announced late friday it has entered into a definitive 144 
billion agreement to acquire staley continental inc a maker of 
corn syrup and foodservice supplies 
the agreement was unanimously approved by staleys board of 
directors tate amp lyle said in a statement 
under the pact tate amp lyles offer of 35 cash per common share 
of staley stock will be increased to 3650 the british company 
said 
staley spokesman david satterfield could not be reached from 
comment calls to his office went unanswered and he did not return 
messages left at his home 
the tender offer is set to expire may 27 at midnight edt tate amp 
lyles offer to buy staley depository shares for 5315 each and 
preferred shares for 105 each would not change under fridays 
agreement 
staley is based in this northwest chicago suburb tate amp lyle 
covets its decaturbased ae staley manufacturing co subsidiary 
the secondlargest us refiner of corn syrup 
staley also owns cfs continental inc a major producer of 
singleserving condiments and other foodservice supplies which 
tate amp lyle would probably sell 
the agreement was announced after new york stock exchange had 
closed staley closed at 36 on the nyse down 1 analysts have 
said staley has a fair market value of about 40 per common share 
tate amp lyle publicly began its takeover bid for all shares of 
staley common stock april 8 at a price of 32 per share 
officials said tate amp lyle held 49 percent of the approximately 
30 million outstanding common shares of staley stock when it began 
takeover efforts and has since obtained an additional 103 million 
shares 
the british company has said it would move staleys headquarters 
back to decatur the central illinois city that was the companys 
home until 1985 
