petition churchgoers in bratislava and other cities reported 
detentions interrogations or other harassment of believers who 
signed or collected signatures 
about 2000 catholics gathered in downtown bratislava the 
capital of slovakia on march 25 to demand religious freedom and 
the appointment of more bishops police drove streetcleaning 
trucks into the crowd to disperse the peaceful rally then used 
water cannons when some protesters didnt leave 
