<TEXT>
nine european nations that profess 
neutrality or nonalignment proposed compromise language friday 
that they hope will lead to a final document at the stalled 
helsinki followup conference 
foreign minister alois mock told reporters the compromise 
contains all the necessary elements of a future concluding 
document for the 35nation conference on security and cooperation 
in europe 
the conference began in november 1986 it is one of several 
called to review compliance with 1975 helsinki accords on military 
security economic cooperation and humanitarian issues signed by 
the soviet union united states canada and all european countries 
except albania 
mock who led the effort by the nine nations said the draft 
offers compromise solutions to those questions which could not be 
resolved by the conference up to now 
mock said it includes some innovative steps to improve 
implementation of human rights provisions including verification 
procedures exchange of information and bilateral meetings to 
discuss violations 
mock said the compromise provides for a human rights conference 
and three followup meetings for contined monitoring 
he said the comprehensive and balanced proposal resulted 
from more than a year of negotiations among austria cyprus 
finland liechtenstein malta san marino sweden switzerland and 
yugoslavia 
a spokesman for the us delegation said privately of the 
proposal we are definitely not ruling it out 
yuri kashlev chief of the soviet delegation described it as a 
positive step 
it may create all conditions for finishing the meeting in a 
couple of months with positive and balanced results he said i 
hope we could do that probably by the end of july 
delegates to the vienna conference have worked since febrary 
1987 on a final document expending upon the original accords 
western nations insist that progress on disarmament and military 
security be balanced by progress on human rights the soviet bloc 
accuses the west of holding security issues hostage to human 
rights 
some western delegates criticized the compromise on human rights 
grounds but mock said 
i dont share the view that the draft falls far short of what 
was proposed originally by the west its a compromise paper 
and compromise means that everybody has to give a little bit 
compared with the original positions 
</TEXT>
