british critics are throwing brickbats at the 
royal shakespeare company after several poorly received productions 
at home and the belated broadway opening of its musical carrie 
which was panned 
the rsc is a national asset i think its time to sound the 
alarm john peter wrote in the sunday times after giving bad 
reviews to two new productions in the companys home theater at 
stratforduponavon william shakespeares birthplace 
peter who had harsh words for the new stagings of shakespeares 
much ado about nothing and william wycherleys the plain 
dealer wrote there was a time not that many years ago when 
you could look to the rsc for expertise excellence and 
enjoyment 
now he said the royal shakespeare company is in trouble 
