an unnervingly shaky start of six productions since march 30 
only across oka a new play by robert holman received 
favorable reviews 
negative reaction to carrie in new york probably will 
generate further talk of a decline peter lamented the prolonged 
devotion of director terry hands to a show the critic called 
frightful 
in 198455 hands productions of much ado about nothing and 
cyrano de bergerac took new york by storm but he spent much of 
the past year on the rock musical adaptation of the stephen king 
horror novel carrie opened may 12 at broadways virginia 
theater after several delays 
the 7 million musical received some sharp notices in new york 
and its initial reception in stratford in february was harsher 
still several critics wondered in print whether the company had 
lost its sense of purpose 
michael coveney in the financial times said carrie was 
enjoyable in a masochistic way and decried hands participation 
in an utter cultural vacuum of dance studio robotics with a hint 
of cultural and classical pretensions 
hands has fared little better in the nonmusical area his 
productions of shakespeares julius caesar and jean genets 
the balcony were received with little enthusiasm 
in an interview with the associated press before taking 
