a judge friday ordered the former 
administrator of drake memorial hospital to spend 30 days in jail 
for falsifying the personnel file of donald harvey the former 
nurses aide who has admitted killing 48 people 
former administrator jan taylor was sentenced after he pleaded 
no contest to falsifying a public document a misdemeanor offense 
taylor was indicted last year on four felony charges of tampering 
with evidence for adding information to harveys file but he 
pleaded no contest to the misdemeanor count as part of a bargain 
with prosecutors 
families of harveys victims were unhappy that taylor 50 was 
able to avoid a trial that could have developed information for use 
