<TEXT>
coastal banc savings association of houston 
acquired four insolvent texas thrifts friday in the first 
consolidation under the governments plan to clean up the troubled 
industry in texas 
the federal home loan bank board will end up spending 1383 
million to merge the following thrifts into coastal alliance 
savings and loan association houston colorado county federal 
savings and loan association columbus security savings and loan 
association dickinson and cameron county savings association san 
benito 
the cost to liquidate the four thrifts would have been 160 
million all deposits will be protected even those that exceed the 
federally insured limit of 100000 officials of the federal home 
loan bank board said 
the consolidation part of the governments so called 
southwest plan boosts coastals assets from 68 million to 
600 million and adds 15 offices to its current five locations 
coastal will continue to operate all branches for three to five 
months but the arrangement then calls for the elimination of half 
of the 20 branches 
this is the beginning and we will begin to see a number of 
future transactions that will provide stability to texas thrifts 
said fhlbb member lawrence j white he called it a good deal for 
the fslic the agency that insures deposits and for depositors 
fhlbb chairman m danny wall said the transaction accomplishes 
the southwest plans key objectives of consolidation strong 
management and the infusion of new capital 
private investors will provide coastal with about 35 million 
in fresh capital in the months following the transaction 
the consolidation is the first since the fhlbb three months ago 
announced its southwest plan to restructure the crippled texas 
thrift industry and cut the number of thrifts in the state by 
onethird 
the important thing here today we got the first olive out of 
the jar indicating the rest should come a lot easier said fhlbb 
member roger martin 
wall said allegations any merger decision would be based on 
political favoritism was an absurdity 
in texas gov bill clements praised the action 
the savings and loan industry is an important part of the 
texas economy the announcement today by the federal home loan bank 
board is a positive step in the direction of restoring health to 
the industry clements said continued negotiations and 
completed mergers under the southwest plan need to proceed in an 
expeditious manner 
